item.title: hello
item.description: Quarto Basics For a demonstration of a line plot on a polar axis, see Figure 1. Code import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt r = np.arange(0, 2, 0.01) theta = 6 * np.pi * r fig, ax = plt.subplots( subplot_kw = {'projection': 'polar'} ) ax.plot(theta, r); ax.set_rticks([0.5, 1, 1.5, 2]); ax.grid(True); plt.show() Figure 1: A line plot on a polar axis
